  "summary": "Security-research / proof-of-concept package: riot-private (npm)",
  "details": "The package riot-private@100.0.0 is a dependency-confusion stub (version 100.0.0, ~600 bytes) whose preinstall hook runs index.js. That file collects the installer's hostname, OS platform, and CPU architecture via os.hostname(), os.platform(), os.arch() and sends them as a JSON POST over HTTPS to hwoapraaaotwtsnourpqddszm5n3kkhvo[.]oast[.]fun/paypalcorp. oast[.]fun is an attacker-controlled callback/interactsh-style domain used for data exfiltration and C2.",
